The paper uses machine learning models to predict safety outcomes in the construction industry, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of NLP to extract attributes from raw incident reports and the use of machine learning models to predict outcomes also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with safety in a specific industry, which could fall under the sub-category of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of different models and experimental setups, which could fall under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
